<div class="row">
  <div class="col-12">
    <h1 class="display-4 text-primary">Pitcher: Library Application</h1>
    <p class="lead">Pitcher application is the central repository of documents that can be automatically synced to subscribing customers.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-sm-4 d-flex flex-column">
    <div class="card flex-grow-1 bg-light">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h5 class="card-title text-info">Documents</h5>
        <p class="card-text">Here is a list of all of the documents held in the library</p>
        <p class="card-text">Only admins users of Pitcher can add new documents or update existing ones.</p>
        <p class="card-text">Whenever a document is updated, it will automatically be pushed to any customer who has subscribed to it.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card-footer mt-auto bg-white">
        <%= link_to 'Documents', documents_path, class: 'btn btn-primary' %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="col-sm-4 d-flex flex-column">
    <div class="card flex-grow-1 bg-light">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h5 class="card-title text-info">Customers</h5>
        <p class="card-text">And here is the list of customers, presented for demonstration only.</p>
        <p class="card-text">In the production application no one will be able to see a list of customers. When a specific user logs in, they will be able to view / edit only their own details.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card-footer mt-auto bg-white">
        <%= link_to 'Customers', customers_path, class: 'btn btn-primary' %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="col-sm-4 d-flex flex-column">
    <div class="card flex-grow-1 bg-light">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h5 class="card-title text-info">Webhooks</h5>
        <p class="card-text">Which customers are connected to which documents is controlled by the webhooks collection. Each webhook contains the information required to send the data to each specific customer application each time the document is updated.</p>
        <p class="card-text">In the production application, only a customer's own webhooks will be visible</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card-footer mt-auto bg-white">
        <%= link_to 'Webhooks', webhooks_path, class: 'btn btn-primary' %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>